    "Content validity.",
    "Content validity refers to the degree to which the instrument measures the construct(s) it purports to measure 71.",
    "COSMIN considers content validity the most important measurement property of an instrument as it should be ensured that the instrument is relevant, comprehensive, and comprehensible with respect to the construct of interest and study population 54.",
    "COSMIN requires that both experts and target population are involved in content validation for content validity to be considered adequate.",
    "Structural validity."
